    "enDesc": "Shaleach Teshalech is a contemporary work that explores the commandment of Shiluach HaKen, sending away a mother bird before taking her young or her eggs. The work is in three parts: the first consists of legal analysis, incorporating the rulings of Rabbi Yosef Shalom Elyashiv and Rabbi Chaim Kanievsky. The second is called the aggadic part, analyzing the mitzvah’s essence, reasons, and rewards. The third is a practical guide for observing this commandment and other laws relating to birds. ",
